verses.verse: Blow the trumpet at the time of the New Moon, At the full moon, on our solemn feast day.
For (Lev. 23:24; Num. 10:10) this is a statute for Israel, A law of the God of Jacob.
This He established in Joseph as a testimony, When He went throughout the land of Egypt, (Deut. 28:49; Ps. 114:1; Jer. 5:15) Where I heard a language I did not understand.
“I removed his shoulder from the burden; His hands were freed from the baskets.

(Ex. 2:23; 14:10; Ps. 50:15) You called in trouble, and I delivered you; (Ex. 19:19; 20:18) I answered you in the secret place of thunder; I (Ex. 17:6, 7; Num. 20:13) tested you at the waters of Meribah. Selah
“Hear, ((Ps. 50:7)) O My people, and I will admonish you! O Israel, if you will listen to Me!
There shall be no ((Ex. 20:3; Deut. 5:7; 32:12); Ps. 44:20; (Is. 43:12)) foreign god among you; Nor shall you worship any foreign god.
(Ex. 20:2; Deut. 5:6) I am the LORD your God, Who brought you out of the land of Egypt; (Ps. 103:5) Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it.
